Opposition parties in the Tshwane council are pushing for stability, following the resignation of mayor Randall Williams. Reporter Pule Letshwiti-Jones has been following this story. #dstv403 TSHWANE - The DA-led coalition in Tshwane wants to see a new mayor appointed as soon as possible. There's a shake-up in the metro's leadership following the resignation of mayor Randall Williams. READ: Tshwane council | Capital city without a mayor - for now The multi-party coalition pushed for a special council sitting on Friday. But speaker Murunwa Makwarela refused that proposal. READ: Tshwane council | Special meeting postponed Instead, there will be a sitting on Tuesday -- much to the frustration of the coalition who argue that the longer the process is delayed, the more service delivery is impacted. * eNCA's Pule Letshwiti-Jones reports.